    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-11-19T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-11-19T18:00:00-05:00" n="809"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d809">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/3799: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Third Secretary of Embassy in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wendelin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-11-19T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 19, 1936—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>198. Your X–323, November 18, 8 p.m. We shall be glad to give our support to any
                    practicable steps aiming to bring about the cessation of artillery and air
                    bombardment of the civil population of Madrid. We shall, therefore, appreciate
                    your keeping us informed as to the reaction of the several Governments to the
                    resolution of the diplomatic corps reported in your telegram under
                    reference.</p>
                <p>In accordance with the request of the Chargé d’Affaires of Argentina the text of
                    the first paragraph of your telegram is being transmitted to the Ministry of
                    Foreign Relations at Buenos Aires through our Embassy there.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
